<br>
The song of rest is only usable if A.)  You're solo xping  B.)  Your pve group has no shammy and 2+skalds C.)  you want to spend 10 minutes kiting somebody.<br>
<br>
The skald was a horrible solo pve class, now it's rising to mediocrity.  It really has no rvr use unless your group has no shammy or healer, even then it's equivalent to friggs 2.  In rvr the spell is fundamentally broken and will rarely if ever be used to any noticable effect.  <br>
<br>
The shout pow/end reduction is nice.  Can dd/mez twice as much.  Again this helps most with pve.  Nice for rvr so you don't run oop in 30 seconds.<br>
<br>
Mainly all this patch added was a downtime reduction for pve and 2 extra attempts at casting each spell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kergon>Kergon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/17/03 6:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=509.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Almost time for new report.</span><hr size=1> I'd like to see skalds have more to do in keep defenses. Mythic seems to want to continue pushing the game towards keep warfare, and that's an area where skalds are severely lacking. <br>
